trans-unit.source: Gets information about the specified pool.
trans-unit.target: Gets information about the specified pool.

trans-unit.source: See <link xlink:href="0e07b9cb-8fdf-4ff7-b707-e964200df0f8" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Common parameters and headers</link> for headers and parameters that are used by all requests related to pools.

trans-unit.source: Replace {pool-id} with the id of the pool that you want to get information about.
trans-unit.target: Replace {pool-id} with the id of the pool that you want to get information about.

trans-unit.source: You can use the HEAD method to obtain just the HTTP status code and headers, excluding the pool details response body: this is useful for determining whether the pool exists or whether it has changed since you last obtained its details.
trans-unit.target: You can use the HEAD method to obtain just the HTTP status code and headers, excluding the pool details response body: this is useful for determining whether the pool exists or whether it has changed since you last obtained its details.

trans-unit.source: You can use it to detect whether the pool has changed between requests.
trans-unit.target: You can use it to detect whether the pool has changed between requests.

trans-unit.source: In particular, you can be pass the ETag with an Update Job request to specify that your changes should take effect only if nobody else has modified the job in the meantime.
trans-unit.target: In particular, you can be pass the ETag with an Update Job request to specify that your changes should take effect only if nobody else has modified the job in the meantime.

trans-unit.source: The last modified time of the pool.
trans-unit.target: The last modified time of the pool.

trans-unit.source: This is the last time at which the pool level data, such as the targetDedicated or enableAutoscale, changed.
trans-unit.target: This is the last time at which the pool level data, such as the targetDedicated or enableAutoscale, changed.

trans-unit.source: It does not factor in node-level changes such as a compute node changing state.
trans-unit.target: It does not factor in node-level changes such as a compute node changing state.

trans-unit.source: The creation time of the pool.
trans-unit.target: The creation time of the pool.

trans-unit.source: The current state of the pool.
trans-unit.target: The current state of the pool.

trans-unit.source: <languageKeyword>active</languageKeyword> – The pool is fully available to run tasks.
trans-unit.target: <languageKeyword>active</languageKeyword> – The pool is fully available to run tasks.

trans-unit.source: A pool enters this state when it is created and remains in this state until it is deleted.
trans-unit.target: A pool enters this state when it is created and remains in this state until it is deleted.

trans-unit.source: <languageKeyword>deleting</languageKeyword> – The user has requested that the pool be deleted, but the delete operation has not yet completed.
trans-unit.target: <languageKeyword>deleting</languageKeyword> – The user has requested that the pool be deleted, but the delete operation has not yet completed.

trans-unit.source: <languageKeyword>upgrading</languageKeyword> – The user has requested that the operating system of the pool’s nodes be upgraded, but the upgrade operation has not yet completed (that is, some nodes in the pool have not yet been upgraded).
trans-unit.target: <languageKeyword>upgrading</languageKeyword> – The user has requested that the operating system of the pool’s nodes be upgraded, but the upgrade operation has not yet completed (that is, some nodes in the pool have not yet been upgraded).

trans-unit.source: The pool may be able to run tasks (with reduced capacity) but this is not guaranteed.
trans-unit.target: The pool may be able to run tasks (with reduced capacity) but this is not guaranteed.

trans-unit.source: The time at which the pool entered its current state.
trans-unit.target: The time at which the pool entered its current state.

trans-unit.source: Indicates whether the pool is resizing.
trans-unit.target: Indicates whether the pool is resizing.

trans-unit.source: There are no changes to the number of nodes in the pool in progress.
trans-unit.target: There are no changes to the number of nodes in the pool in progress.

trans-unit.source: A pool enters this state when it is created and when no operations are being performed on the pool to change the number of dedicated nodes.
trans-unit.target: A pool enters this state when it is created and when no operations are being performed on the pool to change the number of dedicated nodes.

trans-unit.source: <languageKeyword>resizing</languageKeyword> - The pool is resizing; that is, compute nodes are being added to or removed from the pool.
trans-unit.target: <languageKeyword>resizing</languageKeyword> - The pool is resizing; that is, compute nodes are being added to or removed from the pool.

trans-unit.source: <languageKeyword>stopping</languageKeyword> - The pool was resizing, but the user has requested that the resize be stopped, but the stop request has not yet been completed.
trans-unit.target: <languageKeyword>stopping</languageKeyword> - The pool was resizing, but the user has requested that the resize be stopped, but the stop request has not yet been completed.

trans-unit.target: The Azure Guest OS Version currently installed on the virtual machines in the pool.

trans-unit.source: This may differ from targetOSVersion if the pool state is upgrading.
trans-unit.target: This may differ from targetOSVersion if the pool state is upgrading.

trans-unit.source: In this case some virtual machines may be on the targetOSVersion and some may be on the currentOSVersion during the upgrade process.
trans-unit.target: In this case some virtual machines may be on the targetOSVersion and some may be on the currentOSVersion during the upgrade process.

trans-unit.source: Once all virtual machines have upgraded, currentOSVersion is updated to be the same as targetOSVersion.
trans-unit.target: Once all virtual machines have upgraded, currentOSVersion is updated to be the same as targetOSVersion.
